<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Profile - Output Encoding Demo</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            padding: 2rem;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .safe-box {
            border: 2px solid green;
            padding: 1rem;
            margin-top: 1rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }

        .danger-box {
            border: 2px dashed red;
            padding: 1rem;
            margin-top: 1rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
            background: #fff0f0;
        }

        code {
            background: #eee;
            padding: 2px 4px;
            border-radius: 3px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <h1>User Profile: <%= user.username %>
    </h1>

    <div class="safe-box">
        <h2>Safe Bio (Escaped)</h2>
        <p>This uses the <code>&lt;%= %&gt;</code> tags. EJS automatically converts special characters like
            <code>&lt;</code> and <code>&gt;</code> into HTML entities. The XSS payload is rendered harmlessly as plain
            text.</p>

        <!-- SAFE: Output is automatically encoded -->
        <p><strong>Bio:</strong>
            <%= user.bio %>
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="danger-box">
        <h2>Danger Bio (Unescaped - DO NOT USE for user input)</h2>
        <p>This uses the <code>&lt;%- %&gt;</code> tags. It tells EJS to render raw HTML. If we put the bio here, the
            script would execute!</p>

        <!-- UNSAFE: If you uncomment the line below, the XSS attack will run! -->
        <!-- <p><strong>Bio:</strong> <%- user.bio %></p> -->
    </div>
</body>

</html>